4. The Entropy

Domain: thermodynamics and information theory

Entropy measures the number of possible states.
	•	Perfect order → low entropy
	•	Complete randomness → maximum entropy

Living systems exist between these extremes.

Pantheon analogy

Meaning generation requires:
	•	structure (order)
	•	novelty (entropy)

Too ordered → sterile.
Too random → meaningless.

